02:39.492 --> 02:41.403
<i>Here Friday morning.</i>
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:44,996
<i>Now, let's get the stocks here in London.</i>

02:45.031 --> 02:49.604
<i>The Financial Times 100 Index up 11 points,
just above the key 3,800 level.</i>

02:49.869 --> 02:54.545
<i>In the rest of Europe, Frankfurt's DAX
gaining nine points to 2,532.</i>

02:54.707 --> 02:58.711
<i>In Paris, the CAC 40 losing seven,
the weaker franc weighing on the market.</i>

03:13.593 --> 03:15.265
Thank you, Ilsa.

03:16.396 --> 03:18.034
Have a nice day.

03:30.510 --> 03:32.614
<i>...they are on time this morning.</i>

03:33.913 --> 03:35.585
<i>San Francisco's freeways are...</i>

03:51.631 --> 03:53.298
Morning, sir.

03:53.333 --> 03:54.999
<i>Tell me
what we're supposed to do.</i>

03:55.034 --> 04:00.573
<i>You may be perched on majority shares,
but we all get fucked if the actuals crash.</i>

04:00.608 --> 04:02.006
<i>That old man is gonna sink us.</i>

04:02.041 --> 04:06.956
As soon as I have Baer/Grant's
P&L report in hand, I will call you.

04:07.614 --> 04:10.982
<i>- Is that a promise?
- I'm sorry, I'm not aware of that term.</i>

04:11.017 --> 04:14.921
<i>Well, what do I do if Anson calls
about substantiation procedure?</i>

04:14.956 --> 04:17.790
Have your secretary say
you're in a meeting.

04:17.825 --> 04:19.591
Thank you, Jack.

04:19.625 --> 04:21.366
- Yes, Maria?
- Invitations.

04:21.694 --> 04:23.571
- The Museum Gala.
- No.

04:23.796 --> 04:26.833
- Fitzwilliam Botanical Annual Fundraiser.
- No.

04:27.200 --> 04:30.237
- The Hinchberger wedding.
- Hinchberger wedding?

04:31.104 --> 04:34.244
Tuxedos, droning conversations,
I don't think so, no.

04:34.807 --> 04:38.378
I'll send your regrets.
Honestly, why must I bother?

04:38.413 --> 04:40.178
If you don't know about society,

04:40.213 --> 04:43.082
you don't have
the satisfaction of avoiding it.

04:44.183 --> 04:47.027
- Yes?
- I have an Elizabeth on line three.

04:49.055 --> 04:51.831
Your ex-wife.
- I know who it is.

04:53.059 --> 04:54.697
Take a message.

04:55.194 --> 04:56.866
Oh, happy birthday, sir.

04:58.564 --> 05:00.270
Thank you, Maggie.

05:03.036 --> 05:04.569
I don't like her.

05:04.604 --> 05:07.974
I wouldn't mention the following,
but he was very insistent.

05:08.009 --> 05:10.308
- It's a prank.
- What?

05:10.343 --> 05:14.347
A gentleman called requesting lunch.
I assured him you were busy...

05:14.382 --> 05:17.418
- What's his name?
- A Mr. Seymour Butts.

05:19.652 --> 05:22.359
Uhder The Bleachers by Seymour Butts.

05:23.189 --> 05:24.565
I'm sorry?

05:25.558 --> 05:29.529
Cancel my lunch. Make a reservation
at the City Club for myself and Mr. Butts.

05:29.564 --> 05:31.099
My usual table.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.177
Maria, put the reservation under my name.

05:41.574 --> 05:44.510
- Are you ready to order, sir?
- No, I'm still waiting.

05:44.545 --> 05:46.216
This was iced tea.

05:52.552 --> 05:55.828
- Conrad, what a surprise.
- Happy birthday, Nickie.

05:56.356 --> 05:59.735
"Seymour Butts".
I'll never get tired of that one.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.959
That's why it's a classic.

06:01.994 --> 06:04.364
Nice restaurant. They gave me a free jacket.

06:04.399 --> 06:06.309
I'm sure they'll want it back.

06:06.432 --> 06:09.218
- I remember being here.
- I took you here once.

06:09.253 --> 06:12.004
No, I used to buy crystal meth
off the maître d'.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.138
- Really?
- In college.

06:14.173 --> 06:16.880
<i>- Which college?
- Touchè.</i>

06:18.144 --> 06:19.350
Miss me?

06:19.946 --> 06:22.914
As much as that's possible. You look good.

06:22.949 --> 06:26.862
- So do you. To think I was worried.
- Worried about me?

06:27.453 --> 06:31.093
How long's it been since Mom's funeral?
Two, three years.

06:32.325 --> 06:35.428
- I thought you quit.
- I did, it didn't take.

06:35.463 --> 06:38.408
- You can't smoke here.
- I'm with you.

06:38.898 --> 06:42.072
It's illegal to smoke in restaurants
in California.

06:42.468 --> 06:44.170
Fuck California.

06:45.271 --> 06:47.751
- How are you?
- Couldn't be better.

06:49.008 --> 06:50.942
- Elizabeth?
- We're divorced.

06:50.977 --> 06:53.683
She remarried a pediatrician,
or a gynecologist,

06:53.718 --> 06:56.390
or a pediatric gynecologist.
Lives in Sausalito.

06:57.183 --> 06:59.890
That's too bad. I liked her.

07:01.120 --> 07:04.590
- And what about you?
- You don't keep track of me anymore?

07:04.891 --> 07:07.200
Not since family week at rehab.

07:07.794 --> 07:11.397
So what brings you to town, Conrad?
Everything all right?

07:11.432 --> 07:13.266
- Yeah.
- Need anything?

07:13.301 --> 07:14.745
- No.
- Really?

07:15.234 --> 07:16.734
No, I don't need anything from you.

07:16.769 --> 07:20.339
I just found myself laying naked
on a beach near Ibiza

07:20.374 --> 07:22.527
and all of a sudden it clicked,

07:22.562 --> 07:24.681
October 12th, Nickie's birthday.

07:25.378 --> 07:27.915
- October 11 th.
- Whatever.

07:33.419 --> 07:35.694
- This is for you.
- You shouldn't have.

07:36.456 --> 07:39.527
What do you get for the man
who has everything?

07:43.963 --> 07:46.085
Consumer Recreation Services.

07:46.120 --> 07:48.208
Well, I do have golf clubs.

07:48.568 --> 07:49.944
Call that number.

07:50.470 --> 07:53.576
- Why?
- It'll make your life fun.

07:54.674 --> 07:56.641
- Fun.
- You know what that is?

07:56.676 --> 08:00.880
You've seen other people have it.
It's an entertainment service.

08:00.915 --> 08:02.654
An escort service?

08:03.449 --> 08:05.618
A profound life experience.

08:07.353 --> 08:10.766
Sorry. I'll just get...
- Nah, it's all right, just...

08:12.124 --> 08:14.060
- Tell me you'll call.
- I said I would.

08:14.095 --> 08:15.368
No, you didn't.

08:17.697 --> 08:19.642
You still on medication?

08:20.900 --> 08:23.719
- Why would you say that?
You gentlemen ready to order?

08:23.754 --> 08:26.539
- I didn't mean how it sounded.
- I'm not on anything.

08:26.574 --> 08:29.842
I'm not even seeing a shrink.
And I feel great.

08:29.877 --> 08:31.252
Do you mind?

08:35.081 --> 08:37.248
I think you'll like this. I did.

08:37.283 --> 08:39.990
It was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

08:40.520 --> 08:43.159
- I'll call them.
- Do it. For you.

08:43.523 --> 08:46.058
I said I'll call, okay? All right, I'll call.

08:46.093 --> 08:48.595
It's just that... I hate surprises.

08:49.962 --> 08:51.264
I know.

08:53.266 --> 09:00.371
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

09:00.406 --> 09:04.319
<i>Happy birthday, Mr. Van Orton</i>

09:04.544 --> 09:08.253
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

09:13.753 --> 09:17.063
<i>Someone's gotta
drive a stake through Anson's heart.</i>

09:17.356 --> 09:18.824
<i>Have you seen
the profitability report?</i>

09:18.859 --> 09:21.192
Lmagine how unhappy I am.

09:21.227 --> 09:23.563
<i>You'll deal with Anson?
- Correct.</i>

09:23.598 --> 09:25.098
<i>We're furious.</i>

09:25.731 --> 09:28.108
<i>- Sleep well, Nicholas.
- I will.</i>

10:28.194 --> 10:29.760
Good night, Ilsa.

10:29.795 --> 10:34.141
- Dinner's in the oven.
- Thank you. Oh, I saw Conrad today.

10:34.867 --> 10:37.745
- Did you? How is he?
- He's okay.

10:38.104 --> 10:41.414
I think he's in a personal improvement cult.

10:41.707 --> 10:44.119
Well, send my love if you see him again.

10:44.677 --> 10:46.850
- Happy birthday.
- Good night.

11:15.941 --> 11:17.977
<i>...companies that defaulted
on their payments.</i>

11:19.078 --> 11:24.960
<i>The FCC expects to receive
more than $500 million in bids...</i>

11:26.018 --> 11:29.288
<i>- Elizabeth, good evening.
- Happy birthday, Nickie.</i>

11:29.323 --> 11:32.428
11:40. You almost missed it this year.

11:33.426 --> 11:37.830
<i>- Have you had a nice birthday?
- Does Rose Kennedy have a black dress?</i>

11:37.865 --> 11:41.402
I went not once, but twice,
through the spanking machine.

11:42.001 --> 11:43.878
<i>I can only imagine.</i>

11:44.370 --> 11:47.640
<i>- How are you?
- Connie asked me the same thing today.</i>

11:47.675 --> 11:50.711
<i>Connie? Really? I always liked your brother.</i>

11:52.178 --> 11:53.452
Anyway...

11:53.846 --> 11:56.916
<i>I just thought this might be difficult for you.</i>

11:56.951 --> 11:58.827
Just another birthday.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.664
<i>Because of your father.</i>

12:02.421 --> 12:06.892
That's right, he was 48, wasn't he?
I hadn't thought about it until now.

12:08.127 --> 12:09.628
<i>Why do I call?</i>

12:11.063 --> 12:12.974
I honestly don't know.

12:13.265 --> 12:16.200
Please send Dr. Mel and Rachel my best.

12:16.235 --> 12:19.978
<i>She has a little brother on the way.
We did the ultrasound.</i>

12:20.740 --> 12:22.742
Official nuclear family.

12:23.542 --> 12:25.342
You must be very pleased.

12:25.377 --> 12:27.948
<i>We are. We are very pleased.</i>

12:28.647 --> 12:31.150
Well, it's good to talk with you...

12:31.717 --> 12:33.584
<i>I guess I should let you go.</i>

12:33.619 --> 12:37.890
<i>- Take care of yourself.
- You too, Nicholas. I mean that, I really do.</i>

12:37.925 --> 12:39.664
Be well. Bye.

12:40.826 --> 12:43.360
<i>A proposal to encourage small businesses</i>

12:43.395 --> 12:46.398
<i>to provide their employees
with health insurance</i>

12:46.433 --> 12:49.366
<i>is now being debated
by Washington legislators.</i>

12:49.401 --> 12:54.273
<i>The bill, which attaches small-business
health plans to those of larger corporations</i>

12:54.308 --> 12:58.476
<i>is receiving initial support
from a number of key Republican leaders.</i>

12:58.511 --> 13:03.050
<i>However, Democratic lawmakers
are voicing serious concerns about the bill,</i>

13:03.382 --> 13:06.192
<i>claiming that it would undermine local...</i>

13:31.710 --> 13:35.146
I just wanted to make sure
that we understand each other.

13:35.181 --> 13:39.459
Once you get it down on paper,
then you can count on my full support.

13:40.252 --> 13:42.321
- We understand.
- Thank you.

13:42.356 --> 13:43.959
We'll talk soon.

14:20.793 --> 14:23.262
You shouldn't feel
this reflects negatively on you.

14:23.297 --> 14:25.332
<i>I do feel this reflects...</i>

14:25.731 --> 14:27.598
- I received this...
- Just a moment.

14:27.633 --> 14:31.337
<i>- I took these tests in good faith.
I'm sorry you feel that way.</i>

14:31.372 --> 14:34.907
We hope we haven't caused you
any inconvenience.

14:34.942 --> 14:37.011
Thank you for choosing CRS.

14:37.309 --> 14:40.045
Mr. Feingold,
could you assist this gentleman?

14:40.080 --> 14:41.580
Oh, yeah, sure.

14:43.048 --> 14:45.282
Jim Feingold, VP Engineering,
Data Analysis.

14:45.317 --> 14:49.560
I don't know exactly how this works.
My brother sent me this card as a gift.

14:49.955 --> 14:53.308
All right, excellent. Let's get started.

14:53.343 --> 14:56.662
I'm sorry about all this hullabaloo here.

14:56.697 --> 14:59.108
We're... Well, we're still moving.

14:59.798 --> 15:02.471
I got an office around here somewhere.

15:04.737 --> 15:06.739
Do you mind holding that?

15:07.907 --> 15:09.716
Thank you very much.

15:12.344 --> 15:13.544
Thank you.

15:13.579 --> 15:16.448
- Are you hungry? New Moon Cafè.
- No, thank you.

15:16.483 --> 15:18.120
Best in Chinatown.

15:23.122 --> 15:25.534
A gift from Conrad Van Orton.

15:27.059 --> 15:28.692
- Interesting.
- What is?

15:28.727 --> 15:32.062
Your brother was a client
with our London branch.

15:32.097 --> 15:36.375
We do a sort of informal scoring.
His numbers are outstanding.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.009
Really?

15:38.470 --> 15:41.206
- You sure you're not hungry?
- No.

15:41.241 --> 15:43.908
Now, you need to fill out these forms.

15:43.943 --> 15:46.745
There's an application
and a couple of psych tests.

15:46.780 --> 15:48.690
The MMPI and the TAT.

15:49.181 --> 15:53.285
For the financial questionnaire,
don't answer anything you don't feel like.

15:53.320 --> 15:54.889
We'll run a TRW.

15:55.487 --> 15:58.763
"I sometimes hurt small animals.
True or false?"

16:01.393 --> 16:03.896
"I feel guilty when I masturbate. "

16:04.997 --> 16:09.401
Well, I don't write the questions.
I just review the answers.

16:13.706 --> 16:17.476
- What is this for?
- A sense of your capabilities...

16:17.511 --> 16:20.422
No, what is this for? What are you selling?

16:21.747 --> 16:22.918
Oh...

16:23.248 --> 16:25.182
- It's a game.
- A game?

16:25.217 --> 16:28.129
Specifically tailored for each participant.

16:28.687 --> 16:33.325
Think of it as a great vacation.
Except you don't go to it, it comes to you.

16:33.360 --> 16:35.532
What kind of vacation?

16:36.395 --> 16:39.933
- It's different every time.
- Humor me with specifics.

16:40.065 --> 16:41.509
We provide

16:44.737 --> 16:46.503
whatever's lacking.

16:46.538 --> 16:49.675
- What if nothing is lacking?
- May I make two suggestions?

16:49.710 --> 16:52.810
You think I'll participate without knowing...

16:52.845 --> 16:56.155
First, admit to yourself
that it sounds intriguing.

16:57.316 --> 16:59.484
Second, you don't have to decide today.

16:59.519 --> 17:01.618
Take the silly test, fill out the forms.

17:01.653 --> 17:04.890
One day, your game begins.
You either love it or hate it.

17:04.925 --> 17:06.391
Decide then.

17:06.892 --> 17:12.397
You know, we're like
an experiential Book-of-the-Month Club.

17:13.332 --> 17:16.904
You can drop out at any time
with no further obligation.

17:18.637 --> 17:20.616
That was my sales pitch.

17:21.373 --> 17:25.444
- How long will this take?
- An hour for those, an hour for the physical.

17:25.479 --> 17:27.644
- Physical?
- It's a cursory examination.

17:27.679 --> 17:31.422
Turn your head and cough.
You'll be out of here in no time.

18:20.432 --> 18:21.706
Confused.

18:27.539 --> 18:28.710
Risky.

18:32.578 --> 18:33.818
Bloody.

18:38.417 --> 18:39.657
Whoops.

18:59.872 --> 19:03.842
<i>Mr. Sutherland called.
Make it Wednesday.</i>

19:03.877 --> 19:05.978
<i>Anson Baer called about tomorrow.</i>

19:06.013 --> 19:07.244
Tomorrow?

19:07.279 --> 19:11.083
- How much longer will this take?
- Not long, you're almost done.

19:11.118 --> 19:14.291
You said that two hours ago.
Put it back until tomorrow.

19:15.320 --> 19:16.954
<i>...following emotional responses.</i>

19:16.989 --> 19:20.436
<i>You have 0.9 seconds
to enter your emotional response.</i>

19:20.759 --> 19:22.829
<i>Reaction time is a factor.</i>

19:25.631 --> 19:28.667
<i>Please make a selection
for the following emotional responses.</i>

19:28.702 --> 19:32.137
<i>You have 0.9 seconds
to enter your emotional response.</i>

19:35.207 --> 19:36.981
Does this thing end?

19:52.691 --> 19:54.992
- I'm sorry to keep you waiting.
- Don't worry.

19:55.027 --> 19:58.530
It's been terrific spending my entire day
with your crack team.

19:58.565 --> 20:01.833
It's all down to this,
an insurance company requirement.

20:01.868 --> 20:04.069
It states you're aware that The Game exists,

20:04.104 --> 20:06.236
that you're willing to participate in it.

20:06.271 --> 20:12.211
Payment is at your brother's discretion,
dependent on your satisfaction.

20:12.246 --> 20:14.680
If I'm not happy, he doesn't have to pay?

20:14.715 --> 20:17.115
We've never had an unsatisfied customer.

20:17.150 --> 20:19.516
I think you mean "dissatisfied. "

20:19.551 --> 20:21.486
That's right.
You're a left-brain word fetishist.

20:21.521 --> 20:25.024
Initials. And sign there. In blood.

20:25.524 --> 20:27.003
Just kidding.

20:28.827 --> 20:32.130
All right, your copy will be at the front desk
in this folder.

20:32.165 --> 20:34.803
And keep the pen. We'll let you know.

20:39.204 --> 20:41.738
<i>Monday or Tuesday?
Both bad.</i>

20:41.773 --> 20:45.015
<i>- How about tonight?
- I'm working all this evening.</i>

20:46.144 --> 20:48.947
<i>Wednesday's the only possibility right now.</i>

20:48.982 --> 20:51.715
<i>You wanna do dinner?
- Okay.</i>

20:51.750 --> 20:54.718
<i>By the way, I went to CRS.</i>

20:54.753 --> 20:56.954
<i>Really? What'd you think?</i>

20:56.989 --> 21:00.190
<i>Well, they seemed
just a little bit disorganized.</i>

21:00.225 --> 21:03.213
<i>When I did it in London,
they'd been around a while.</i>

21:03.248 --> 21:06.201
<i>- Are you gonna do this?
- I haven't decided yet.</i>

21:09.501 --> 21:13.438
It's like getting in on the ground floor
of the next Disneyland.

21:13.473 --> 21:16.441
CRS won't go public.
They're family-owned.

21:17.476 --> 21:21.253
Stranger things have happened.
No, they haven't, actually.

21:22.080 --> 21:25.151
They opened here.
The Game in San Francisco?

21:25.617 --> 21:28.461
See? They're doing fine without any of us.

21:30.322 --> 21:32.028
A scotch and soda.

21:33.925 --> 21:36.746
- Nicholas, how are you?
- James, good evening.

21:36.781 --> 21:39.567
- Got new members here?
- I believe so, sir.

21:40.499 --> 21:43.402
- Put their next round on me.
- Gotcha, sir.

21:46.605 --> 21:51.843
No, no, no. Last time I played Pebble,
I swore I'd never pick up a club again.

21:53.145 --> 21:55.245
Well, speaking about games,

21:55.280 --> 21:58.351
I couldn't help but overhear you talking
about CRS.

22:00.686 --> 22:03.858
The reason I mention it
is I took the test today.

22:03.893 --> 22:07.031
- The Montgomery street office.
- You did? Kudos.

22:07.326 --> 22:10.661
- So yours hasn't started yet?
- Not yet.

22:10.696 --> 22:14.609
That was one of the questions I had for you.
What is it?

22:15.334 --> 22:18.036
- What is it?
- The eternal question.

22:18.071 --> 22:19.703
You know, I envy you.

22:19.738 --> 22:24.209
I wish I could go back
and do it for the first time, all over again.

22:26.678 --> 22:29.818
Here's to new experiences.

22:33.685 --> 22:36.621
Excuse me, I've gotta go. Night, Ted.

22:36.656 --> 22:38.998
- Nicholas.
- Nice to meet you.

22:42.861 --> 22:46.274
- So you played recently?
- About a year ago.

22:46.998 --> 22:49.637
I was working in Los Angeles.

22:49.935 --> 22:52.869
I hear the London office is very good, too.

22:52.904 --> 22:55.884
Sounds like a lot
of fantasy role-playing nonsense.

22:58.610 --> 23:00.646
You wanna know what it is?

23:00.979 --> 23:02.753
What it's all about?

23:03.281 --> 23:06.227
John, chapter 9, verse 25.

23:06.852 --> 23:10.355
I haven't been to Sunday school
in a long time.

23:10.390 --> 23:13.893
"Whereas once I was blind, now I can see. "

23:16.628 --> 23:19.802
Good night, Nicholas. Best of luck.

23:20.565 --> 23:22.009
Good night.

23:36.214 --> 23:38.557
If the Baer/Grant meeting

23:40.185 --> 23:42.494
is not held tomorrow,

23:43.221 --> 23:45.667
it may as well not be held at all.

23:47.959 --> 23:51.129
When Mr. Van Orton boards his plane
on the morrow,

23:51.164 --> 23:53.530
he will have every agreement
and addendum,

23:53.565 --> 23:56.767
the complete closing package,
flawlessly revised.

23:56.802 --> 24:00.305
So you'll miss another opera
you would have slept during anyway.

24:01.373 --> 24:02.773
We now have an opportunity
to show our client

24:02.808 --> 24:06.153
how well we will rise
to his exhilarating challenge.

24:08.280 --> 24:10.414
<i>- Yes.
Nicholas Van Orton?</i>

24:10.449 --> 24:13.016
<i>- Who is this?
- This is Cynthia from CRS.</i>

24:13.051 --> 24:16.321
<i>- How did you get this number?
- We've processed your application.</i>

24:16.356 --> 24:19.529
<i>- I'm in a meeting...
- I'm afraid it was rejected.</i>

24:20.525 --> 24:21.625
I beg your pardon?

24:21.660 --> 24:25.095
<i>You shouldn't feel
this reflects negatively on you.</i>

24:25.130 --> 24:28.099
<i>- This is ridiculous.
- Thank you for thinking of CRS.</i>

24:29.601 --> 24:32.604
- Anything wrong?
- No, nothing.

24:35.440 --> 24:38.844
<i>You may hang up,
or press "pound" for more options.</i>

24:38.879 --> 24:41.654
<i>Oh, this is Conrad, leave a message.</i>

24:42.647 --> 24:46.390
Yes, Connie, it's Nicholas.
Give me a ring when you get in.

24:46.618 --> 24:52.357
Oh, regarding your birthday present,
things are a little crazy right now,

24:52.392 --> 24:54.191
I don't know if I can fit it in my schedule.

24:54.226 --> 24:57.571
We'll talk about it at dinner tomorrow.
Thanks. Bye.

25:30.896 --> 25:32.067
Hello?

26:33.291 --> 26:37.762
<i>...resulting rise of unemployment
and decline in viable small businesses.</i>

26:38.296 --> 26:41.299
<i>Meanwhile, Republican leaders argue
that its passage would be</i>

26:41.334 --> 26:44.473
<i>the very stimulant
a sluggish economy needs.</i>

26:45.036 --> 26:48.173
<i>No one has expressed an opinion
as to how it will impact</i>

26:48.208 --> 26:51.207
<i>the pampered existence
of Nicholas Van Orton.</i>

26:51.242 --> 26:54.544
<i>The one thing on which both
Democrats and Republicans agree</i>

26:54.579 --> 26:59.233
<i>is that most Americans harbor
serious doubts about the economic future.</i>

26:59.268 --> 27:03.888
<i>A recent poll suggests a staggering
57% of American workers believe</i>

27:03.923 --> 27:06.791
<i>there is a very real chance
they will be unemployed</i>

27:06.826 --> 27:09.225
<i>within the next five to seven years.</i>

27:09.260 --> 27:13.708
<i>But what does that matter
to a bloated, millionaire fat cat like you?</i>

27:14.833 --> 27:18.935
<i>Stock markets rose
both domestically and abroad</i>

27:18.970 --> 27:21.671
<i>after the announcement
of stronger than expected earnings</i>

27:21.706 --> 27:25.910
<i>by several hi-tech companies,
but dipped again after reports</i>

27:25.945 --> 27:28.515
<i>that Nicholas Van Orton had sneezed.</i>

27:31.449 --> 27:35.920
<i>Are you gonna spend the rest of the evening
prying at that clown's mouth?</i>

27:37.122 --> 27:38.288
I... I don't...

27:38.323 --> 27:41.633
<i>It's frustrating for me
if you don't pay attention.</i>

27:42.661 --> 27:44.162
What is this?

27:44.929 --> 27:48.103
<i>This is your game, Nicholas,
and welcome to it.</i>

27:49.534 --> 27:52.571
<i>I'm here to let you in on a few ground rules.</i>

27:53.071 --> 27:56.313
<i>You've received the very first key
and others will follow.</i>

27:56.574 --> 28:00.178
<i>You won't know where you'll find them
or how you'll need to use them,</i>

28:00.213 --> 28:02.123
<i>so keep your eyes open.</i>

28:02.514 --> 28:06.689
<i>- How do you... You can see me?
- Let's save the questions till after.</i>

28:09.287 --> 28:11.027
How does this work?

28:12.657 --> 28:15.899
<i>There's a tiny camera
looking at you right now.</i>

28:17.762 --> 28:20.765
<i>- That's impossible.
- You're right. Impossible.</i>

28:21.132 --> 28:23.976
<i>You're having a conversation
with your television.</i>

28:27.072 --> 28:28.744
<i>It's miniaturized.</i>

28:31.576 --> 28:34.056
<i>Do you know how dangerous that is?</i>

28:38.883 --> 28:40.083
Mr. Van Orton?

28:40.118 --> 28:41.786
<i>And in domestic news, in southern...</i>

28:41.821 --> 28:43.553
Yes, Ilsa, what is it?

28:43.588 --> 28:46.068
- Is everything all right?
- Fine...

28:46.558 --> 28:49.125
<i>...in a petroleum processing
plant yesterday...</i>

28:49.160 --> 28:52.130
I've finished for the evening.
Will you be needing anything else?

28:52.165 --> 28:53.797
No, thank you.

28:53.832 --> 28:56.366
- Good night.
- Good night, then.

28:56.401 --> 28:59.704
<i>...broke out
in a petroleum processing plant yesterday.</i>

28:59.739 --> 29:01.538
<i>Several workers were injured...</i>

29:01.573 --> 29:04.280
<i>- Who's that?
- Never mind who that is.</i>

29:04.676 --> 29:06.611
<i>You wanna know
how a camera got into your home.</i>

29:06.646 --> 29:07.851
Yes, I would.

29:16.221 --> 29:17.324
<i>Cold.</i>

29:19.324 --> 29:20.530
<i>Colder.</i>

29:24.763 --> 29:25.900
<i>Warm.</i>

29:30.602 --> 29:31.842
<i>Warmer.</i>

29:47.819 --> 29:49.457
<i>Write this number down.</i>

29:49.687 --> 29:53.057
<i>It's a 24-hour
Consumer Recreation Services hotline,</i>

29:53.092 --> 29:54.791
<i>for emergencies only.</i>

29:54.826 --> 29:57.695
<i>But don't call asking
what the object of the game is.</i>

29:57.730 --> 30:00.903
<i>Figuring that out is the object of the game.</i>

30:01.332 --> 30:05.280
<i>Good luck,
and congratulations on choosing CRS.</i>

30:05.570 --> 30:09.108
<i>...threatened to have
the American ambassador expelled.</i>

30:09.774 --> 30:13.244
<i>The US State Department responded quickly
with a formal apology,</i>

30:13.279 --> 30:16.748
<i>and announcement
of the ambassador's immediate removal.</i>

30:37.235 --> 30:39.112
Help me out here, huh?

30:39.804 --> 30:41.613
I used to be in Nam.

30:54.452 --> 30:58.161
<i>If you'd like to
make a call, please hang up and try again.</i>

32:14.232 --> 32:15.767
May I help you?

32:19.837 --> 32:21.213
What is it?

32:25.410 --> 32:26.513
What?

32:35.753 --> 32:37.095
Thank you.

32:50.501 --> 32:51.570
Bud?

32:54.138 --> 32:55.912
Can you help me out?

32:57.775 --> 33:00.346
I need some toilet paper, I ran out.

33:02.580 --> 33:04.719
Just go into the next stall.

33:07.318 --> 33:09.161
Come on, help me out.

33:10.355 --> 33:14.362
Hello?

33:19.530 --> 33:22.967
- Didn't expect to see you here.
- I wanted to wish you luck.

33:23.002 --> 33:26.337
- You been up all night?
- I checked it. Personally.

33:26.372 --> 33:28.771
I appreciate that.
Go home and get some sleep.

33:28.806 --> 33:31.115
- You sure you don't want me along?
- No, I'll be fine.

33:32.610 --> 33:34.851
Nice shirt.
- Don't ask.

33:35.580 --> 33:36.717
<i>Ciao.</i>

34:01.539 --> 34:03.639
All these years,

34:03.674 --> 34:07.111
the first time ever you step foot
in these offices,

34:07.146 --> 34:09.344
it's to ask me to step down.

34:09.380 --> 34:11.482
You promised to meet
the projections, Anson.

34:11.516 --> 34:13.824
$1.60 a share is what you said.

34:14.252 --> 34:17.289
I don't think this visit comes as a surprise.

34:17.688 --> 34:20.456
- The projections were too optimistic.
- Admittedly, yes.

34:20.491 --> 34:23.781
Our EPS was 150 last quarter.
We are up eight cents per share.

34:23.815 --> 34:27.072
The expectations were ten.
The expectations meant everything.

34:28.032 --> 34:30.569
Will you hold me to it over pennies?

34:30.935 --> 34:33.036
My stock is falling,
I don't know about yours.

34:33.072 --> 34:35.271
Those pennies are costing millions.

34:35.306 --> 34:39.911
Give me next quarter.
If you still feel this way, vote your shares.

34:39.946 --> 34:42.083
Today is what counts, Anson.

34:45.116 --> 34:48.620
You... You intractable son of a bitch.

34:49.587 --> 34:52.072
If your father could see you now.

34:52.108 --> 34:54.524
- What?
- Your father was a friend.

34:54.559 --> 34:56.859
A friend.
God damn it, I watched you grow up.

34:56.893 --> 35:02.600
Because you went fishing with my father,
I should watch you throw my money away?

35:02.635 --> 35:04.079
- I was...
- I'm not finished.

35:04.635 --> 35:08.173
You misspoke before
when you said you're stepping down.

35:09.040 --> 35:10.678
I am firing you.

35:11.609 --> 35:14.453
Action is taken, confidence is restored.

35:15.446 --> 35:17.413
- The stock goes up.
- No.

35:17.448 --> 35:20.155
There's no Baer/Grant Publishing...

35:20.785 --> 35:25.097
No Baer/Grant Publishing
without Anson Baer.

35:25.923 --> 35:27.156
Where's Stewart Grant?

35:27.191 --> 35:30.194
Probably out sailing,
enjoying his golden years,

35:30.229 --> 35:32.970
wondering where the hell you are, Anson.

35:33.164 --> 35:34.506
I'm sorry.

35:35.500 --> 35:36.910
You failed.

35:40.972 --> 35:45.978
I have prepared a severance package
that is more than equitable.

35:47.545 --> 35:50.116
Valid until this evening.

35:52.450 --> 35:54.554
I could fight you on this.

35:55.052 --> 35:59.694
If I leave without your signature,
this agreement begins to disintegrate.

36:00.758 --> 36:06.298
Benefits shrink, options narrow,
and your compensation will be shriveled.

36:12.770 --> 36:16.479
I think it's in your best interest, Anson, to...

36:32.623 --> 36:35.899
Well, I guess this is your lucky day.

36:37.962 --> 36:40.601
My lawyers will be in touch with you.

37:13.331 --> 37:16.432
Excuse me,
has Conrad Van Orton left a message?

37:16.467 --> 37:19.709
- I'll check right away, Mr. Van Orton.
- Thank you.

37:26.110 --> 37:28.249
I'm so sorry. Here.

37:28.646 --> 37:32.750
- Please don't do that.
- I'm so sorry. I wasn't even looking.

37:32.785 --> 37:35.620
- I'm really having a bad day.
- How about a bad month?

37:35.655 --> 37:38.691
You did almost the same thing
to me last week.

37:39.023 --> 37:40.289
- Here.
- Don't do that.

37:40.324 --> 37:43.703
Just get me some napkins
and some soda water.

37:44.028 --> 37:47.907
It looks like the cleaning bill's
gonna be more than the suit.

37:49.033 --> 37:50.671
I don't think so.

37:52.036 --> 37:54.405
- It was an accident, sir.
- Terrific.

37:54.440 --> 37:56.145
I said I was sorry.

37:59.877 --> 38:01.978
- Asshole.
- Christine.

38:02.013 --> 38:06.100
- Mr. Van Orton is a valued customer.
- Fine. Then you kiss his ass.

38:06.135 --> 38:10.187
- Don't you talk to me like that.
- I apologized, I offered to help.

38:10.222 --> 38:12.156
- Clean out your locker.
- What?

38:12.191 --> 38:13.657
You heard me.

38:16.761 --> 38:18.961
I'm terribly sorry, Mr. Van Orton.

38:18.996 --> 38:22.238
Will this table suit you
for a complimentary meal?

38:22.500 --> 38:24.035
It'll be fine.

38:32.143 --> 38:34.680
- I'll fetch your waiter.
- Thank you.

38:35.546 --> 38:36.922
Check, sir.

38:59.704 --> 39:01.906
Fuck you and your vichyssoise, you little...

39:01.941 --> 39:04.208
Miss? Pardon me, miss.

39:04.243 --> 39:05.908
Great, it's you.

39:05.943 --> 39:10.789
I don't know how this works,
but do you have something for me? I...

39:12.683 --> 39:16.387
- I received this note.
- What are you babbling about, psycho?

39:16.422 --> 39:18.487
I need to know what is going on.

39:18.522 --> 39:21.090
I'm going on my second job this month,

39:21.125 --> 39:23.730
and now it looks
like I'm going on unemployment.

39:24.462 --> 39:28.466
- Maybe I should try to explain...
- Don't explain, just fuck off.

39:31.369 --> 39:33.280
Son of a bitch.

39:33.838 --> 39:37.012
I'm trying to... I am apologizing.

39:50.154 --> 39:51.928
Jesus. What is this?

39:55.960 --> 39:58.060
- What's with him?
- He just fell down.

39:58.095 --> 40:00.664
Sir, can you hear me?
Do you know what to do?

40:00.699 --> 40:02.336
I don't even know if he's breathing.

40:04.235 --> 40:07.682
Move your head. Don't stand there, get help.

40:09.006 --> 40:10.815
Hey, hey. It's okay.

40:11.809 --> 40:14.755
- We're gonna get help.
- How do we know he's real?

40:15.246 --> 40:18.317
There's piss in his pants,
is that real enough for you?

40:19.316 --> 40:22.092
- Holy God.
- He's turning blue.

40:23.487 --> 40:24.897
Police.

40:36.434 --> 40:39.437
- You have to fill these forms out.
- I don't know this man.

40:39.472 --> 40:41.270
I can't get involved.

40:41.305 --> 40:43.672
- I have to detain you.
- Detain me?

40:43.707 --> 40:46.159
- The report's gotta be filled out.
- She can do it.

40:46.194 --> 40:48.612
Ride with your wife,
we'll meet at the hospital.

40:48.647 --> 40:50.350
Two blocks away.

40:50.385 --> 40:52.053
She's not my wife.

40:58.189 --> 41:02.426
This is insane. Ten minutes ago,
I was enjoying a quiet little dinner.

41:02.461 --> 41:04.337
I received this note.

41:08.332 --> 41:10.772
- He's breathing, isn't he?
- Yes.

41:10.807 --> 41:13.213
Is the siren entirely necessary?

41:14.672 --> 41:15.878
Right.

41:27.017 --> 41:30.521
Let's just talk to someone
who can get this over with.

41:30.556 --> 41:31.761
Hang on.

41:32.623 --> 41:35.365
They need your driver's license number.

41:49.273 --> 41:53.548
- Oh, no, you've got to be kidding.
- What is happening?

41:53.583 --> 41:57.823
This is what I was trying to explain to you.
This is a game.

41:59.116 --> 42:00.783
- A what?
- It's a company.

42:00.818 --> 42:04.959
They plan elaborate pranks.
I don't really understand it myself.

42:06.290 --> 42:08.991
What are you talking about? This is a...

42:09.026 --> 42:12.405
The lights, they went out.
A hundred people ran away.

42:13.364 --> 42:17.401
Oh, so you mean the guy who just
pissed himself and turned blue was...

42:17.436 --> 42:19.039
Sorry about that.

42:20.371 --> 42:21.872
You should be.

42:26.143 --> 42:28.213
Why are they involving you?

42:28.913 --> 42:33.589
There's gotta be a fucking flashlight.

42:34.518 --> 42:35.860
Oh, great.

42:41.425 --> 42:44.895
I thought that guy was gonna die.
I gave him mouth-to-mouth.

42:44.930 --> 42:46.704
I'll see you around.

42:49.466 --> 42:52.276
- How do you know that's the way?
- I don't.

43:04.014 --> 43:07.393
Where'd you all go,
you motherfucking frat boys?

43:09.920 --> 43:11.592
You'd better hide.

43:31.875 --> 43:33.046
Lobby?

44:17.588 --> 44:21.126
My brother got me this gift certificate
to this company.

44:22.159 --> 44:25.896
Well, I got the key out of the mouth

44:25.931 --> 44:28.899
of this wooden clown.

44:30.167 --> 44:31.577
Never mind.

44:36.073 --> 44:37.813
I don't like this.

44:47.084 --> 44:48.283
No signal.

44:48.318 --> 44:52.391
What is the going rate
for a "trapped-in-the-elevator" adventure?

44:53.424 --> 44:56.158
- Don't even think about it.
- Why not?

44:56.193 --> 45:00.397
Read the sign. "Warning, do not attempt
to open if elevator stops. "

45:00.432 --> 45:04.037
- "Use emergency... "
- "Phone"? If there was one.

45:04.072 --> 45:07.643
"And wait for help. "
So, let's just wait for help.

45:18.582 --> 45:21.722
- Okay, I'll give you a boost.
- You can go first.

45:22.086 --> 45:26.056
This is not gallantry.
If I don't lift you, how will you get up?

45:26.091 --> 45:28.323
I don't know. You pull me up.

45:28.358 --> 45:30.838
- It's easier my way. Step up.
- No.

45:31.195 --> 45:34.141
- Oh, please.
- I'm not wearing any underwear.

45:35.933 --> 45:37.878
Okay? There, I said it.

45:42.773 --> 45:43.910
Okay.

46:00.224 --> 46:03.534
- We can use this like a ladder.
- My hero. Let's go.

46:07.164 --> 46:08.802
I don't think so.

46:11.235 --> 46:12.577
Thank you.

46:20.878 --> 46:22.755
Damn it, my briefoase!

46:26.917 --> 46:28.327
I'll wait.

46:28.952 --> 46:31.329
Not as if anybody could open it.

46:39.229 --> 46:42.464
- Wait a minute. This is CRS.
- What's CRS?

46:42.499 --> 46:46.970
The company I was telling you about,
that gave me the gift certificate.

46:47.005 --> 46:48.915
This is their building.

46:55.779 --> 47:00.193
We'll wait for security to come,
and we'll just explain.

47:00.651 --> 47:03.563
They'll love that! Explain for both of us.

47:04.454 --> 47:07.660
Wait.

47:22.973 --> 47:26.310
We don't want to draw any attention.
We're just out for a stroll.

47:26.345 --> 47:27.511
Run!

47:32.349 --> 47:33.555
We can't fit down there!

47:41.425 --> 47:44.761
Are you trying to ditch me?
- I'm not responsible...

47:44.796 --> 47:45.967
I'm not the one who started running!

47:47.231 --> 47:49.870
Yeah, well, I'm not the one
that started this...

48:06.416 --> 48:07.951
- Get up there!
- I'm going!

48:09.820 --> 48:11.458
Here.

48:12.522 --> 48:14.626
Climb. Climb.

48:24.534 --> 48:27.378
So where's your modesty
around attack dogs?

48:38.715 --> 48:40.956
Shut up! Stupid fucking dogs.

48:45.255 --> 48:47.530
Let me guess. I go first.

48:59.369 --> 49:03.146
- There goes $1,000.
- Your shoes cost $1,000?

49:03.874 --> 49:05.375
That one did.

49:11.615 --> 49:13.250
Here, come on.

49:16.853 --> 49:20.027
Watch out for nails and rats.

49:21.758 --> 49:24.033
There should be a fire escape.

49:44.614 --> 49:46.184
That's classic.

49:47.918 --> 49:49.192
Why me?

49:53.523 --> 49:54.967
Who are you?

49:56.159 --> 49:57.899
Nicholas Van Orton.

49:58.595 --> 50:01.075
What are you, a tsar or something?

50:01.932 --> 50:03.308
All right.

50:04.034 --> 50:07.947
I think, if we drop from here,

50:09.072 --> 50:10.607
the garbage will break our fall.

50:11.141 --> 50:12.278
I think not.

50:12.609 --> 50:14.019
Be careful!

50:19.383 --> 50:21.918
What the fuck are you looking at?

50:21.953 --> 50:24.022
Oh, shit.

50:50.180 --> 50:52.091
Table for two, please.

50:58.288 --> 50:59.554
Where are we going?

50:59.589 --> 51:02.831
That tall, bright building?
It's right near there.

51:08.432 --> 51:10.309
Everything okay, miss?

51:11.034 --> 51:13.446
Yeah. How are you doing?

51:15.005 --> 51:16.984
San Francisco's finest.

51:28.151 --> 51:30.893
Is there some place I could throw this?

51:31.721 --> 51:34.428
There's a waste basket beside the desk.

51:36.526 --> 51:39.871
I think I have a fresh sweatshirt
for you somewhere.

51:40.730 --> 51:42.368
That'd be great.

51:46.736 --> 51:49.744
You know, you've never even asked me
my name.

51:49.779 --> 51:52.752
The maître d' said your name was Christine.

51:53.844 --> 51:55.254
Oh, right.

51:56.346 --> 51:58.553
I guess I'll call you a cab.

52:02.686 --> 52:05.428
- You got a shower in your office?
- Yeah.

52:06.056 --> 52:07.824
You an athlete or something?

52:08.992 --> 52:14.771
No, I'm an investment banker.
I move money from one place to another.

52:18.835 --> 52:21.941
Actually, would you mind
if I just quickly rinsed off?

52:23.273 --> 52:24.308
No.

52:25.742 --> 52:30.588
- Is there a towel I could use?
- Yeah, it's behind the door.

52:31.114 --> 52:33.890
- Oh. I'll just be a second.
- No problem.

52:36.853 --> 52:42.200
Listen, I know the owner of the City Club.
I'd be happy to give him a call if you'd like.

52:42.492 --> 52:45.097
Don't. It was a shitty job anyway.
I overreacted.

52:46.663 --> 52:47.732
I...

52:49.499 --> 52:50.773
I have a confession to make.

52:52.969 --> 52:58.175
Someone gave me 400 bucks
to spill drinks on you as a practical joke.

52:58.210 --> 53:00.642
Really? And what did they say?

53:00.677 --> 53:03.980
They said, "300," I said, "400,"
they said, "The guy in the gray flannel suit. "

53:04.015 --> 53:08.360
I think I said,
"The attractive guy in the gray flannel suit?"

53:34.377 --> 53:38.256
Mr. Van Orton. I was afraid
you weren't going to make it back.

53:46.156 --> 53:48.592
<i>- Hello?
- Mr. Van Orton? It's Maria.</i>

53:48.627 --> 53:49.658
<i>I thought I should call.</i>

53:49.693 --> 53:52.460
<i>- What time is it?
- It's 11:00.</i>

53:52.495 --> 53:55.498
<i>I rescheduled your meeting
with Allison and Dietrich.</i>

53:55.533 --> 53:58.033
No, I'll be in there in an hour.

53:58.068 --> 54:02.672
Can you... I left my briefoase
at 1019 Montgomery Street.

54:02.707 --> 54:04.973
Can you check
with Lost and Found, please?

54:05.008 --> 54:08.778
<i>Anson Baer is at the Ritz-Carlton.
He's requesting dinner.</i>

54:08.813 --> 54:10.512
We'll see about that.

54:10.547 --> 54:15.120
<i>And the Hotel Nikko called to say
they have your American Express card.</i>

54:15.385 --> 54:17.592
<i>You left it there last night?</i>

54:18.488 --> 54:20.790
<i>- Should I send someone?
- Give me the number.</i>

54:20.825 --> 54:24.032
<i>- 565-1111.
- I'll call you back.</i>

