01:28:54.162 --> 01:28:57.438
- That's impossible.
- They already got it, Nicholas.

01:28:58.800 --> 01:29:00.574
They got everything.

01:29:06.974 --> 01:29:09.911
<i>This is
the Sutherlands. Please leave a message.</i>

01:29:09.946 --> 01:29:12.412
Sam, I have checked them all.

01:29:12.447 --> 01:29:16.690
I don't know how,
but they have drained my accounts.

01:29:17.652 --> 01:29:20.520
They're trying to kill me. Call the cops.

01:29:20.555 --> 01:29:24.093
I've got one of them right here.
We'll make her testity.

01:29:24.559 --> 01:29:29.440
I know how this sounds,
but you call me, on my cellular.

01:29:30.098 --> 01:29:31.975
And you be careful.

01:29:32.734 --> 01:29:35.771
He cut your card in half, so...

01:29:37.505 --> 01:29:38.915
My treat.

01:30:17.745 --> 01:30:19.849
You take two sugars, right?

01:30:20.982 --> 01:30:22.358
Never mind.

01:30:28.956 --> 01:30:31.392
My name's not Christine. It's...

01:30:31.427 --> 01:30:33.269
Who fucking cares?

01:30:34.395 --> 01:30:37.569
It's just money.
You should be glad you're alive.

01:30:38.166 --> 01:30:40.873
I'd rather not talk about it right now.

01:30:42.270 --> 01:30:46.240
- Someone like you...
- How many times have you done this?

01:30:46.275 --> 01:30:48.982
- What?
- These scams, con games. How many?

01:30:50.144 --> 01:30:51.210
Lots.

01:30:51.245 --> 01:30:56.421
Whatever bullshit you pulled in the past,
this is more than just me.

01:30:57.151 --> 01:30:59.995
This is pension plans, payrolls.

01:31:00.755 --> 01:31:02.962
This is $600 million.

01:31:16.571 --> 01:31:19.813
<i>- Yes.
- Nick, it's Sam. I got your message.</i>

01:31:20.107 --> 01:31:21.916
<i>I was disturbed.</i>

01:31:22.076 --> 01:31:25.446
<i>- So what are we gonna do?
- I've been on the phone already.</i>

01:31:25.481 --> 01:31:27.789
<i>Nicholas, your funds are intact.</i>

01:31:28.783 --> 01:31:30.938
<i>Nothing's been touched.</i>

01:31:30.973 --> 01:31:33.094
I checked on them myself.

01:31:33.321 --> 01:31:35.189
Who is it?
- I made the calls.

01:31:35.224 --> 01:31:36.929
<i>Nothing's changed.</i>

01:31:37.191 --> 01:31:39.967
<i>Not one cent is unaccounted for.</i>

01:31:40.361 --> 01:31:41.727
Who is it?

01:31:41.762 --> 01:31:46.100
- My attorney says nothing is missing.
- He's in on it.

01:31:46.135 --> 01:31:49.669
<i>Stay where you are until I get there.</i>

01:31:49.704 --> 01:31:53.174
<i>- Sutherland's in on it.
- Nicholas, I have another call.</i>

01:31:53.341 --> 01:31:55.821
<i>Give me your precise location.</i>

01:31:56.310 --> 01:31:57.584
<i>Nicholas?</i>

01:32:01.549 --> 01:32:03.460
Gotta get out of here.

01:32:09.557 --> 01:32:11.536
How did they get to him?

01:32:12.393 --> 01:32:13.769
Why did...

01:32:16.330 --> 01:32:18.673
I wouldn't worry about it.

01:32:24.138 --> 01:32:25.776
What do you mean?

01:32:26.474 --> 01:32:28.647
It's out of your hands.

01:32:51.299 --> 01:32:53.745
Cellular calls can be intercepted.

01:32:55.169 --> 01:33:00.174
All those calls you made,
B of A, France, Switzerland...

01:33:00.209 --> 01:33:02.278
You were talking to us.

01:33:03.377 --> 01:33:07.620
You filled in the blanks,
access codes and passwords.

01:33:07.882 --> 01:33:10.555
Stuff even your lawyer didn't have.

01:33:12.119 --> 01:33:14.326
We have it now so we're done.

01:33:27.902 --> 01:33:29.574
Bye, Nicholas.

01:35:44.371 --> 01:35:47.113
Embassy? American?

01:35:48.409 --> 01:35:49.751
Thank you.

01:35:54.415 --> 01:35:57.384
Things have happened and it's important...

01:36:01.322 --> 01:36:04.769
No money, no identification, no passport.

01:36:07.495 --> 01:36:09.235
What happened to you?

01:36:09.930 --> 01:36:11.568
Where to begin...

01:36:13.634 --> 01:36:15.977
- It's complicated.
- It always is.

01:36:20.207 --> 01:36:26.213
I was on holiday alone
and I was robbed by two men...

01:36:26.248 --> 01:36:27.589
Robbed?

01:36:28.482 --> 01:36:30.584
What hotel were you staying at?

01:36:30.619 --> 01:36:33.530
I don't remember. I...

01:36:35.189 --> 01:36:37.464
Have you gone to the police?

01:36:38.492 --> 01:36:40.369
I don't speak Spanish.

01:36:42.797 --> 01:36:45.364
And I just need enough to get out of here.

01:36:45.399 --> 01:36:49.123
We'll help with
the local law enforcement if you want.

01:36:49.158 --> 01:36:52.848
As far as money is concerned,
can I make a suggestion?

01:36:53.808 --> 01:36:55.787
You say you were mugged?

01:36:56.410 --> 01:36:58.753
And they didn't take that watch?

01:37:00.614 --> 01:37:05.563
How much is a watch like that worth?
A couple of hundred at least.

01:37:09.123 --> 01:37:13.730
A man with a watch like that doesn't
necessarily have a passport problem.

01:38:38.479 --> 01:38:39.821
Excuse me.

01:38:40.881 --> 01:38:43.554
Can I have your attention, please?

01:38:47.888 --> 01:38:49.230
Thank you.

01:38:50.758 --> 01:38:54.034
Anybody here going to San Francisco?
I need a ride.

01:38:56.830 --> 01:39:01.506
I got $18.78...

01:39:02.970 --> 01:39:05.279
For a ride to San Francisco.

01:39:10.878 --> 01:39:12.118
Anybody?

01:40:59.920 --> 01:41:01.558
Keep the change.

01:41:05.392 --> 01:41:08.896
Conrad Van Orton.
Could you ring his room, please?

01:41:09.530 --> 01:41:11.270
One moment, please.

01:41:15.402 --> 01:41:17.142
Is there a problem?

01:41:17.404 --> 01:41:19.038
- You're here for Conrad Van Orton?
- Yes.

01:41:19.073 --> 01:41:22.144
- I'm the hotel manager.
- Where is my brother?

01:41:23.777 --> 01:41:27.349
- Will you come with me?
- Wait a minute. Is there trouble?

01:41:28.148 --> 01:41:30.787
Sir, this is a private matter for you.

01:41:42.396 --> 01:41:46.036
There were complaints by other guests,
damage to his room.

01:41:46.166 --> 01:41:48.500
We did our best
to accommodate his behavior.

01:41:48.535 --> 01:41:53.416
- His behavior?
- There was an incident a few days ago.

01:41:54.508 --> 01:41:56.851
A nervous breakdown, they said.

01:41:57.244 --> 01:41:59.121
The police took him.

01:41:59.580 --> 01:42:02.390
They left this address in case anyone came.

01:42:02.516 --> 01:42:04.723
It's a hospital in Napa, sir.

01:42:05.752 --> 01:42:07.492
I'm terribly sorry.

01:42:24.738 --> 01:42:27.548
<i>Elizabeth,
I need to borrow your car.</i>

01:42:28.408 --> 01:42:32.356
Nickie, what happened to you? I mean...

01:42:33.714 --> 01:42:37.117
- Look at you.
- What happened? I don't know.

01:42:37.152 --> 01:42:40.521
There's things I have to do
and I need your car.

01:42:40.556 --> 01:42:42.694
Of course you can have it.

01:42:45.225 --> 01:42:47.637
Can't I get you something to eat?

01:42:48.195 --> 01:42:51.574
You know you're the only person
that I can trust?

01:42:53.734 --> 01:42:58.338
Everyone else... If Sam Sutherland calls,
don't tell him you talked to me.

01:42:58.373 --> 01:43:01.250
You lie to him and whatever else happens...

01:43:02.843 --> 01:43:06.847
Coffee, English muffin and your water.

01:43:08.348 --> 01:43:11.418
This bottle is open.
Who opened this bottle?

01:43:11.453 --> 01:43:13.519
- I opened it.
- I don't want it.

01:43:13.554 --> 01:43:17.900
I want an unopened bottle.
I don't want ice, just the glass.

01:43:18.959 --> 01:43:20.165
Please.

01:43:24.198 --> 01:43:27.042
Nickie, talk to me. You're scaring me.

01:43:28.435 --> 01:43:33.475
- I don't even know what you're saying.
- I'm sorry, Liz, I don't mean to. I'm sorry.

01:43:35.342 --> 01:43:41.918
I've been thinking the last couple of days,
I've had some spare time...

01:43:45.385 --> 01:43:47.888
And I wanted to tell you that...

01:43:49.356 --> 01:43:51.699
I understand why you left me.

01:43:52.526 --> 01:43:54.938
And I know that I resented it.

01:44:00.200 --> 01:44:04.978
I want to apologize to you
for shutting you out...

01:44:06.306 --> 01:44:08.410
For not being there.

01:44:08.675 --> 01:44:10.375
I hope you can forgive me.

01:44:10.410 --> 01:44:13.213
<i>You're tired.
You've been on the go for days.</i>

01:44:13.248 --> 01:44:14.513
There's nothing to forgive.

01:44:14.548 --> 01:44:19.394
<i>Pain sets in.
The onset of a migraine headache.</i>

01:44:20.187 --> 01:44:24.066
<i>If this sounds all too familiar,
relief is here at last.</i>

01:44:24.324 --> 01:44:26.291
No. You bastards!

01:44:26.326 --> 01:44:28.863
<i>Taggarene. For nearly a decade...</i>

01:44:29.663 --> 01:44:31.972
How did you find me here?

01:44:33.300 --> 01:44:37.179
<i>Taggarene is strong medicine
for headaches, toothaches...</i>

01:44:38.038 --> 01:44:39.539
He's an actor.

01:44:39.740 --> 01:44:42.880
<i>So if you trust your doctor,
trust Taggarene.</i>

01:44:44.144 --> 01:44:46.419
He's an actor on television.

01:44:48.548 --> 01:44:50.493
Some day I'll explain.

01:44:51.285 --> 01:44:53.890
Could I borrow your Yellow Pages?

01:45:15.008 --> 01:45:16.384
Okay...

01:45:16.543 --> 01:45:19.023
New Moon Cafè.

01:45:19.479 --> 01:45:21.219
Best in Chinatown.

01:45:22.582 --> 01:45:25.919
Get out of the car, fucker.
Open the door and leave it running.

01:45:25.954 --> 01:45:28.954
- You're making a mistake.
- Get out of the car.

01:45:28.989 --> 01:45:34.700
- Get the fuck out of the car.
- I am extremely fragile right now.

01:45:44.338 --> 01:45:46.909
New Moon Cafè.

01:45:48.241 --> 01:45:51.962
- He does commercials.
- You know how many customers we have?

01:45:51.997 --> 01:45:55.684
I know he ordered from you.
It went to Montgomery Street.

01:45:57.584 --> 01:45:59.384
Can anybody help me?

01:45:59.419 --> 01:46:03.560
He's an actor, like one of these people
you have up here on your...

01:46:16.069 --> 01:46:18.981
Hey, where are you taking my picture?

01:46:19.639 --> 01:46:24.178
We were hoping he could audition today.
He would be perfect for this part.

01:46:24.911 --> 01:46:29.349
<i>This will break his heart.
- Is there any place to contact him?</i>

01:46:29.384 --> 01:46:33.385
<i>His beeper's here.
He took the kids to the zoo.</i>

01:46:33.420 --> 01:46:38.191
<i>- The zoo? That's very sweet. Which zoo?
- The one with the white tiger.</i>

01:46:42.362 --> 01:46:44.865
Lionel Fisher, I love your work.

01:46:47.768 --> 01:46:51.306
Okay, please, can I... I got my kids.

01:46:52.706 --> 01:46:54.239
Get rid of them.

01:46:54.274 --> 01:46:59.018
All right, guys. Snack time.
More snacks. Go, go, go.

01:47:00.847 --> 01:47:02.382
Look...

01:47:02.983 --> 01:47:05.952
It was just a job. Nothing personal.

01:47:05.987 --> 01:47:08.887
I play my part. Improvise a little.

01:47:08.922 --> 01:47:13.200
- It's what I'm good at.
- I need to talk to who's in charge.

01:47:13.460 --> 01:47:16.863
Nobody knows. Nobody gets the big picture.

01:47:16.898 --> 01:47:20.232
Tammy, Alex, cut it out!
Why do they do that?

01:47:20.267 --> 01:47:24.340
The offices are empty.
I need to find out where they are.

01:47:27.240 --> 01:47:32.846
Look, they own the whole building.
They just move from floor to floor.

01:47:32.881 --> 01:47:36.020
And you work for them, right?
You can get me in.

01:47:36.783 --> 01:47:38.950
- No, I can't.
- Yes, you can.

01:47:38.985 --> 01:47:44.291
Tell them the police called. Tell them
I'm gonna blow the whistle on them.

01:47:44.326 --> 01:47:48.204
What whistle? There's no whistle.
This is very dangerous.

01:47:51.097 --> 01:47:53.634
I don't think you understand.

01:47:55.569 --> 01:48:01.519
Right now I am extremely dangerous.

01:48:05.045 --> 01:48:08.082
Michael, guys, come on, we're leaving.

01:48:19.626 --> 01:48:22.538
- Well, we're here.
- Drive in.

01:48:28.068 --> 01:48:32.205
What are you gonna do anyway?
You won't get your money back.

01:48:32.240 --> 01:48:36.153
I don't care about money.
I'm pulling back the curtain.

01:48:36.643 --> 01:48:38.645
I wanna meet the wizard.

01:48:41.014 --> 01:48:42.083
Hey.

01:48:44.518 --> 01:48:48.898
- He's eyeing us like Tiffeny Towers.
- Pull in where they won't see you.

01:49:11.411 --> 01:49:13.584
Shit. Stay down.

01:49:18.652 --> 01:49:22.759
- You're not allowed to be here.
- They called me back. I got a fitting.

01:49:23.990 --> 01:49:25.560
He's with me.

01:49:28.662 --> 01:49:30.937
- You don't need me.
- Shut up.

01:49:31.798 --> 01:49:33.504
Get in there.

01:49:34.434 --> 01:49:36.504
Cuff him to the rail.

01:49:41.775 --> 01:49:43.049
What floor?

01:50:02.128 --> 01:50:03.629
You're fucked!

01:50:06.566 --> 01:50:08.800
- Where?
- They hired me over the phone.

01:50:08.835 --> 01:50:11.738
- Where'd you pick up your checks?
- It was a different floor.

01:50:11.773 --> 01:50:14.608
- Guess.
- This way. Sort of.

01:50:14.643 --> 01:50:16.519
I don't know. I...

01:50:19.579 --> 01:50:21.217
Take it easy now.

01:50:50.276 --> 01:50:52.653
This is gonna be a surprise.

01:51:11.631 --> 01:51:12.973
Oh, fuck!

01:51:15.368 --> 01:51:17.347
What are you doing here?

01:51:17.837 --> 01:51:19.577
Back from the dead.

01:51:29.582 --> 01:51:32.562
Nicholas, you're not about to shoot anyone.

01:51:32.952 --> 01:51:34.431
Turn around.

01:51:42.462 --> 01:51:44.566
You're gonna come with me.

01:51:45.231 --> 01:51:46.903
Everybody, down!

01:52:07.854 --> 01:52:09.594
Where are we going?

01:52:18.932 --> 01:52:20.172
Stop!

01:52:28.808 --> 01:52:32.881
- What do you think you're doing?
- You tell me!

01:52:33.646 --> 01:52:36.649
Who's behind this? Who did this to me?

01:52:36.684 --> 01:52:38.518
- Why?
- What do you mean, why?

01:52:38.553 --> 01:52:40.520
How deluded can you be?

01:52:40.854 --> 01:52:45.632
It could've been any asshole with
a couple of hundred million in the bank.

01:52:45.892 --> 01:52:49.996
Get your boss up here.
Tell him I'm gonna shoot someone.

01:52:50.031 --> 01:52:51.696
They won't do it.

01:52:51.731 --> 01:52:55.935
Oh, yes, they will. Get someone up here
because I'm gonna kill you.

01:52:55.970 --> 01:53:00.140
They'll let me die.
You're not in a position to threaten anyone.

01:53:00.175 --> 01:53:02.643
- Where'd you get that?
- What?

01:53:03.109 --> 01:53:05.643
That gun. That's not an automatic.

01:53:05.678 --> 01:53:09.649
- What are you talking about?
- Where'd you get the gun?

01:53:09.684 --> 01:53:12.352
- This is my gun.
- We searched the house.

01:53:12.387 --> 01:53:14.822
Well, I guess you missed this.

01:53:14.857 --> 01:53:17.257
We got a real goddamn gun up here.

01:53:18.424 --> 01:53:21.628
- This is fake. It's part of your game.
- Don't start with me!

01:53:21.663 --> 01:53:24.564
- Listen to me!
- Don't you fucking start with me!

01:53:24.599 --> 01:53:25.764
This is all the game.

01:53:25.799 --> 01:53:29.400
Bullshit. They shot
that guy Feingold, Fisher.

01:53:29.435 --> 01:53:34.611
- They killed him. I saw them kill him.
- What did you really see this whole time?

01:53:34.808 --> 01:53:39.814
Special effects. Squibs, like in the movies.
Nicholas, listen!

01:53:40.880 --> 01:53:45.260
He's got a real gun. Okay, I'll put it down!

01:53:47.086 --> 01:53:49.721
Fisher's behind that door. He's an actor.

01:53:49.756 --> 01:53:52.859
- You're trying to kill me.
- No one's trying to kill you.

01:53:52.894 --> 01:53:55.560
You're about to make a big mistake.

01:53:55.595 --> 01:53:58.598
There was a safety net.
The taxi, there was a diver.

01:53:58.633 --> 01:54:01.601
- We were shot at with blanks.
- That's not true.

01:54:01.636 --> 01:54:03.635
It's what you hired us for.

01:54:03.670 --> 01:54:08.084
They're waiting on the other side
of that door with champagne.

01:54:08.474 --> 01:54:11.454
It's Conrad. Conrad's there!

01:54:11.711 --> 01:54:13.479
It's your birthday party.

01:54:13.514 --> 01:54:15.083
You stop lying!

01:54:17.851 --> 01:54:19.455
Let me show you.

01:54:20.820 --> 01:54:22.594
Don't you move.

01:54:23.656 --> 01:54:26.295
He's got a gun! Get back from the door!

01:54:40.440 --> 01:54:41.919
You shot him.

01:54:49.415 --> 01:54:52.327
Someone call an ambulance!

01:55:12.872 --> 01:55:14.214
He's dead.

01:55:19.212 --> 01:55:21.157
We thought you knew.

01:55:25.418 --> 01:55:27.954
How did you let this
get so out of hand?

01:55:27.989 --> 01:55:30.934
He wouldn't listen to me.

01:55:34.794 --> 01:55:37.240
We went through this over and over.

01:55:41.167 --> 01:55:43.434
The mark is your responsibility.

01:55:43.469 --> 01:55:48.341
You never, never let the mark take over.

01:55:50.777 --> 01:55:52.256
I'm sorry.

01:55:55.248 --> 01:55:58.752
You had a walkie-talkie.
- I used it.

01:56:02.088 --> 01:56:07.196
We're going to jail. We're all going to jail
for the rest of our lives.

01:56:17.570 --> 01:56:18.810
Oh, God.

01:56:20.273 --> 01:56:21.547
Nicholas!

01:56:56.676 --> 01:57:00.624
<i>We got him. He's in the bag.
He came in right on target.</i>

01:57:01.147 --> 01:57:03.786
<i>Stand by for a further medical.</i>

01:57:03.950 --> 01:57:07.659
<i>Keep them back until
we clear away the breakaway glass.</i>

01:57:09.055 --> 01:57:10.855
Don't open your eyes.

01:57:10.890 --> 01:57:13.993
This is breakaway glass
but it can still cut you.

01:57:15.395 --> 01:57:18.967
I'm just gonna take a look.
I'm gonna check your pulse.

01:57:24.337 --> 01:57:26.942
Take it easy. That was quite a fall.

01:57:58.604 --> 01:58:00.515
Happy birthday, Nickie.

01:58:12.952 --> 01:58:14.487
What is this?

01:58:15.421 --> 01:58:17.525
It's your birthday present.

01:58:37.443 --> 01:58:41.015
I had to do something.
You were becoming such an asshole.

01:58:52.158 --> 01:58:54.727
Ladies and gentlemen,
my brother, Nicholas Van Orton.

01:59:30.263 --> 01:59:33.039
Amazing. I just wanted to tell you.

01:59:34.367 --> 01:59:36.346
This was the best ever.

01:59:38.004 --> 01:59:42.308
Thank God you jumped. If you didn't,
I was supposed to throw you off.

01:59:44.443 --> 01:59:48.080
We have to head home.
I just wanted to say goodbye.

01:59:48.115 --> 01:59:51.322
Rachel, sweet dreams.

01:59:53.419 --> 01:59:56.729
Thanks, Mel, for coming.
Sorry about your car.

01:59:57.290 --> 01:59:59.736
- I left it at the zoo.
- No problem.

02:00:06.465 --> 02:00:08.638
Happy birthday, Nicholas.

02:00:10.670 --> 02:00:13.047
I'll call you. I really will.

02:00:28.754 --> 02:00:32.257
Nicholas, I haven't a clue
what this is all about,

02:00:32.292 --> 02:00:35.761
but your taste in champagne is excellent,
as always.

02:00:35.796 --> 02:00:37.900
It was a great entrance.

02:00:39.031 --> 02:00:40.831
I want you to know...

02:00:40.866 --> 02:00:45.678
No, please.
I've never been happier in my whole life.

02:00:45.972 --> 02:00:49.351
I thank you and my wife thanks you.

02:00:51.110 --> 02:00:53.089
Thank you for coming.

02:00:53.579 --> 02:00:55.251
Thank you, Sam.

02:00:57.917 --> 02:01:01.159
- What's this?
- This is...

02:01:02.755 --> 02:01:04.359
The bill.

02:01:05.324 --> 02:01:07.463
The bill?
- Keep the pen.

02:01:09.729 --> 02:01:11.572
Thank you. Both.

02:01:18.871 --> 02:01:20.171
Wanna split it?

02:01:20.206 --> 02:01:23.710
Oh, God, yes, please.
I'll take you up on that.

02:01:25.077 --> 02:01:26.647
Oh, my God.

02:01:30.950 --> 02:01:32.759
Thank you, Connie.

02:01:36.355 --> 02:01:40.997
What happened to that waitress?
What was her name...

02:01:41.427 --> 02:01:42.727
Christine?

02:01:42.762 --> 02:01:47.301
She said something about catching a plane.
I saw her hailing a cab.

02:02:06.452 --> 02:02:07.794
Christine?

02:02:10.456 --> 02:02:11.696
I...

02:02:11.991 --> 02:02:15.802
- I didn't get a chance to say goodbye.
- Well, thank you. I...

02:02:15.928 --> 02:02:18.931
I never did ask you your name, did I?

02:02:18.966 --> 02:02:22.640
No. It's Clare.

02:02:23.135 --> 02:02:26.203
So you're catching a plane?

02:02:26.238 --> 02:02:29.273
Yeah, we have a gig starting
next week in Australia.

02:02:29.308 --> 02:02:32.745
- You gonna shear some more sheep?
- Just a walk-on this time.

02:02:32.780 --> 02:02:34.986
Well, when you get back...

02:02:37.850 --> 02:02:40.421
Maybe we could have some dinner.

02:02:41.454 --> 02:02:43.866
You don't know anything about me.

02:02:44.190 --> 02:02:45.600
No, I don't.

02:02:46.258 --> 02:02:47.825
So you tell me.

02:02:47.860 --> 02:02:50.129
- Well...
- Where you're from.

02:02:51.530 --> 02:02:54.510
Originally? Oklahoma.

02:02:55.368 --> 02:02:56.869
Colorado?

02:03:00.239 --> 02:03:02.685
I've been doing this way too long.

02:03:04.877 --> 02:03:06.412
You know...

02:03:08.581 --> 02:03:12.824
Would you like to
have a coffee with me at the airport?

